{
  "texts": [
    "• Building the Utility Matrix: A user-item utility matrix is constructed from the ratings data, wherein rows represent users, columns represent items, and cell values are the ratings given by users to items.",
    "Missing values are filled with zeros, indicating no interaction.",
    "• Matrix Decomposition: The utility matrix is decomposed using Truncated SVD.",
    "This step results in a set of matrices that capture latent factors representing hidden user and item attributes.",
    "• Identifying Patterns and Correlations: The system analyzes the decomposed matrices to identify patterns and correlations in user preferences."
  ]
}